            <h3>How do Entrepreneurs get profiled on the Zaka website?
            </h3>
            <p>Entrepreneurs can directly apply to join the Zaka community of entrepreneurs but this does not lead to listing into the Zaka website. The profiling into the zaka website is done by Zaka assessment team once an entrepreneur is vetted, and under
              goes Zaka investment preparation program. Entrepreneurs can also be listed into the zaka website on recommendation from pre-qualified zaka partners (incubators and accelerators).
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="s-project-details">
            <h3>How do I get started as Zaka Entrepreneur?</h3>
            <p>Simply click on the Sign Up icon and register through the simple step by step process as guided. Once you have filled the basic information required, paid the registration fees, Zaka assessment team will identity and verify your profile. If
              qualified, you will be contacted by Zaka to conduct a physical due diligence after which you will be admitted into Zaka investment preparation program. On completion, you will be profiled into Zaka platform and can commence borrowing.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="s-project-details">
            <h3>What is Zaka Investment Readiness program?</h3>
            <p>This is a two-session accelerated bootcamp for investment readiness. The program aim to inculcate value-based business management principles and ready the business to accept investment (both debt and equity). The program is facilitated by highly
              qualified consultants. Alumni of Zaka Investment Readiness program automatically join the Zaka Business Club. The program costs Kes10,000.00</p>
          </div>
          <div class="s-project-details">
            <h3>What is Zaka Business Club?</h3>
            <p>This is a community of entrepreneur who’ve undertaken the Zaka Investment Program and have been profiled in the Zaka platform. The club members access the following benefits; Belong to a community united by a shared code of conduct</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Network and share best practices</li>
              <li>Peer to peer mentorship</li>
              <li>Business leadership training from consultants</li>
              <li>Business management DIY tools</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="s-project-details">
            <h3>Who can I get a Zaka loan?</h3>
            <p>Zaka connects investors to investment ready entrepreneurs. Zaka therefore identifies, prepares for investment and profiles into Zaka.co.ke financially excluded entrepreneurs who can’t access growth capital and affordable sources of credit due to
              various barriers in the formal financial system. Zaka team and partners (incubators and accelerators) conduct a thorough due diligence followed by investment preparation program to build their capacity. At Zaka, we are sector-agnostic therefore
              entrepreneurs from all sectors can borrow through Zaka platform.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="s-project-details">
            <h3>How does Zaka determine the interest rates on loans?</h3>
            <p>Zaka does not dictate interest rates to entrepreneurs or investors, all Zaka does is provide an indicative rate based on the entrepreneurs risk profile. The investors is then at liberty to make an offer to the entrepreneur. The entrepreneurs can
              either a) accept, b) reject, or c) negotiate. This way a fair interest acceptable to both the lender and borrow is charged.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="s-project-details">
            <h3>Can a Zaka investor offer a loan at 0% interest?</h3>
            <p>Yes, social investors and philanthropic lenders keen to support say, a women group can offer a loan at zero % interest. In this case, the investor only makes a 2.5% fee to support the operations of zaka platform and meet additional costs of
              including training, financial literacy classes and clients’ mobilization.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="s-project-details">
            <h3>Can I be both a lender (Investor) and a borrower (entrepreneur)?</h3>
            <p>Yes, you can register into the Zaka platform as an investor and a borrower. You however cannot borrow and lend at the same time, you can either borrow or invest at any one given time.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="s-project-details">
            <h3>As an investor in Zaka, do I need to fund the entire loan?</h3>
            <p>No, Zaka allows for syndicated loans using a crowdfunding approach. There are many individual lenders who come together to contribute towards a posted loan.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="s-project-details">
            <h3>Am I guaranteed that I get 100% repaid?</h3>
            <p>Zaka conducts a thorough due diligence on all the entrepreneurs posted on the website. The spirit of Zaka is to overcome the barriers that have existed barring credible entrepreneurs from accessing growth capital, key among them being
              security/collateral – we therefore drive a trust-based approach. Zaka therefore does not guarantee repayment for any loans crowdfunded on the Zaka website. Past borrowing history does not always guarantee future repayment, and Zaka investors should
              bare this in mind while making loans that could lead to losing some or all of the lender’s principal</p>
          </div>
          <div class="s-project-details">
            <h3>Why should I pay Zaka registration fees and that too before getting the loan?</h3>
            <p>Zaka has an in-house assesment team which conducts due diligence and carefully assess each borrower profile which involves cost, time and effort. The registration fees caters for these cost and also meets the maintenance cost for the portal.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="s-project-details">
            <h3>What does it cost an entrepreneur to access Zaka portal</h3>
            <p>The entrepreneur pays a one-off registration fees of Kes 5,000.00 and on application and approval of loan, pays 4% for processing and payment gateway fees. The investor does n</p>
