            How does Zaka attain sustainability? Zaka is a for profit limited liability company. Zaka therefore takes a fee from the platform users. An entrepreneur pays 2.5% success fees on successful crowdfunding while the investor equally charged a 2.5% for
            administration, continuous investment monitoring and investment preparation.
            <h3>Who are Zaka Partners?</h3>
            <p>These are mainly organizations who share similar values with Zaka and work to provide incubation, acceleration and enterprise support services to targeted entrepreneurs. This way, over and above Zaka investment preparation program, Zaka is able to
              reach more entrepreneurs spread across a wide geography more effectively. These partners work in entrepreneur communities and vet borrowers, provide services and ensure “know-your-customer” policy is maintained.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="s-project-details">
            <h3>What’s the difference between a Straight Zaka loan and a Zaka loan?</h3>
            <p>Zaka loans are loans crowd sourced through Zaka website and offered by a network of zaka investors. Zaka Straight loans are made off Zaka International’s balance sheet don’t involve a Zaka investors.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="s-project-details">
            <h3>How does the money for the loan get to each borrower?</h3>
            <p>Loan funds reach borrowers through the money transfer platform provided by Nouveta. This includes Mpesa, Airtel money, Equitel and Paypal. For Zaka loans, once the loan is fully crowdfunded on Zaka, funds are transmitted to the borrower via the
              above referenced payment gateway.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="s-project-details">
            <h3>What is the due diligence process on Zaka loans?</h3>
            <p>Entrepreneurs profiled on Zaka Platform are identified and vetted by either a Zaka Partner (Accelerator or Incubator) or Zaka Investment preparation team. For the partners, Zaka conducts a due diligence on the Enterprise support provider,
              Accelerator and/or Incubators.</p>
            Zaka Team conduct due diligence by following the following steps:
            <li>a) Conduct know-your-customer process,</li>
            <li>
              b) Entrepreneur selection criteria – Entrepreneur of high integrity, with good, long-term growth prospects,
            </li>
            <li>c) Client visit and interview entrepreneur,</li>
            <li>
              d) Reference check and review,
            </li>
            <li>e) Enter into 1 month investment preparation program,
            </li>
            <li>f) Graduation and registration into Zaka Website. With this, Entrepreneurs can be connected to the Zaka network of investors. What happens if a loan doesn’t get fully funded on the Zaka Platform? Loans are posted into Zaka platform for a period
              of 30 days, after which they are put in the back for an additional 15 days. If the loans are not fully funded, then they are passed over to Zaka Straight loans for further review and possible top-up. There are possible cases where entrepreneurs won’t
              receive their loan even after profiling the same on Zaka website. When this happens, the investors who will have committed funds will get the same reimbursed. These should be rare cases and Zaka will do absolute best to ensure such cases are
